With good roads connecting cities and main towns and rural areas investors can put up industries.Young people and other investors should be ready to grab opportunities presented by these road projects. On November 25, when President Kenyatta and ODM leader Raila Odinga launched the Constitution of Kenya (Amendment) Bill, 2020 at the KICC, the State House choir corrupted the song ‘Safari ya Bamba ni Machero’ by replacing the word ‘machero’ with ‘rero’.
Perhaps aware delegates may have wondered why the lyrics had changed, the MC Peter Wanjohi quickly announced that it was because the 45-km Mariakani-Bamba road immortalised by the song to bemoan its desolate condition had since been rehabilitated by Kenya Rural Roads Authority. 



