Standard Gauge Railway
KeNHA is constructing the Sh30 billion-540km Mau Mau road traversing Kiambu, Murang’a, Nyeri and Nyandarua counties, the Nairobi Expressway, Thika-Kenol-Sagana-Marua-Nyeri dual carriageway, Nairobi-Nakuru-Mau Summit and the Mwingi-Marimanti road.
About 49 KeNHA projects are complete, including Kisumu-Kakamega Road, Wembuye-Kitale, Kakamega-Webuye Chebilat-Chabera, Ol Jororok-Dondori, Voi-Mwatate and Rumuruti-Naibor.
The government is also currently working on an estimated 4, 100 kilometers as part of the Sh300 billion-10, 000 kilometers of Low Volume Seal Roads (LVSR) program, with estimated 2,900 kilometers of roads already completed.
The construction of the Sh4.1 billion Malindi-Salagate road in Kilifi , which links Malindi town and Tsavo East National Park, is expected to ease connectivity and attract international tourists and investors to the Coast as well as the 53 km Samburu-Kinango road that connects Kwale with the busy Mombasa-Nairobi highway and the Likoni-Lunga Lunga road at a cost of Sh2 billion. 





Kura has 47 ongoing projects across the nation, with 16 already completed or under way, including roads under the Nairobi Regeneration Plan.
Further, beside the Standard Gauge Railway line, the president has been rehabilitating the Meter Mauge railway lines, with the 177 km Nairobi- Nanyuki having done its maiden freight last week since 1990s and already, has attracted several investors in the region.



